       Less than 10% of EU aid money reaches the countries where it is most=
 needed, according to a study that found levels of assistance had dropped f=
or the second year running.

The EU and its member states remain the biggest development donor group in =
the world ? investing ?71.9bn ($61bn) in 2018, more than half of global aid=
 ? but its contribution was 5.8% lower than in 2017, the European NGO netwo=
rk, Concord, found in its AidWatch report.

Progress on meeting the UN target of spending 0.7% of gross national income=
 on aid, laid down in 1970, has gone into reverse, said the group. Their re=
search showed that aid decreased to 0.47% of the EU?s combined GNI last yea=
r, compared with 0.49% in 2017 and 0.51% in 2016.

